Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - This paper clearly deals with the diffusion of information in social networks, both physical and online. 
2. cs.SN (Social and Multiagent Networks) - The paper also deals with the interaction between individuals in a network, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The impact of online social networks on society is a key aspect of this paper, making it relevant to this sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The SIR epidemic model used in the paper falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions web sites such as YouTube, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
